SUMMARY:Build\, Scale & Govern AI Agents
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nIn this session\, you’ll explore 
 how to design scalable and reliable multi‑step AI agents by combining ag
 entic RAG techniques\, MCP‑based tool use\, and proven agent design patt
 erns. We’ll break down how these components work together to create agen
 ts that reason effectively\, coordinate tasks\, and integrate seamlessly w
 ith external systems.\n\nThrough practical examples and reusable patterns\
 , you’ll learn how to build agents that can scale across teams\, extend 
 to complex workflows\, or be adapted for your personal projects. You’ll 
 leave with a toolkit of approaches you can immediately apply to accelerate
  your agent development journey.\n\n--------------------------------------
 ---------\n[The Java Script AI Build-a-thon](https://aka.ms/JSAIBuildathon
 )\n\n📌 This session is a part of a series! Learn more [here](https://de
 veloper.microsoft.com/reactor/series/S-1628/?wt.mc_id=meetup_S-1628_webpag
 e_reactor)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/microsoft-reactor-toronto/events/3132
 44697/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260207T001404Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260207T001404Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_312718527@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260311T023314Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260311T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260311T130000
SUMMARY:Build Secure\, Observable\, Production-ready Agents with a Control
  Plane
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\n**Brought to you by Microsoft and N
 VIDIA**\n\nOrchestrate\, secure and observe agents enabling advanced AI wo
 rkflows. Reliable agent orchestration requires clear separation between co
 ntrol and execution. In this joint session\, Microsoft and NVIDIA present 
 a multi-agent architecture where Foundry Agent Service coordinates GPU-bac
 ked agents running on Azure Container Apps.\n\nUsing a document processing
  scenario with multiple open-source models including NVIDIA Nemotron model
 s\, we show how agents route requests\, apply security controls\, and moni
 tor execution across GPU workloads\, producing consistent and explainable 
 results suitable for production environments.\n\n🔔 This session will be
  presented in two time zones. For our later stream\, [click here](https://
 developer.microsoft.com/reactor/events/26683?wt.mc_id=meetup_26660_webpage
 _reactor)\n\n[This session is a part of a series\, learn more here](https:
 //developer.microsoft.com/reactor/series/S-1590/?wt.mc_id=meetup_26660_web
 page_reactor)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/microsoft-reactor-toronto/events/3127
 18527/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260104T204147Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260104T204147Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
