DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260311T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260311T160000
SUMMARY:Azure Decoded: Getting Ready for the Migrate & Modernize Summit
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nThe Migrate & Modernize Summit is w
 here Microsoft brings together the latest thinking on how to move faster o
 n Azure — using AI‑powered\, agentic approaches to modernize infrastru
 cture\, databases\, and applications.\n\nIn this Azure Decoded episode\, y
 ou’ll get a sneak peek at what’s coming: the key themes you’ll hear 
 across Summit keynotes and breakouts\, the real‑world migration and mode
 rnization scenarios being spotlighted\, and why this event matters if you
 ’re planning your next move to Azure. We’ll also highlight the skillin
 g opportunities connected to the Summit\, including the Migrate & Moderniz
 e Foundations Virtual Training Day\, so you’ll know how to get ready\, w
 hat to focus on during the event\, and how to turn what you learn into act
 ion afterward.\n\n**What you’ll learn:**\n- What to expect at the Migrat
 e & Modernize Summit — key themes like agentic AI\, Azure Copilot\, Azur
 e Migrate\, and modernization pathways across compute\, data\, and apps.\n
 - How Microsoft approaches migration and modernization today — from asse
 ssment and planning to modernization\, security\, and optimization after t
 he move.\n- How to skill up before and after the Summit — including how 
 the Migrate & Modernize Foundations VTD and learning paths help turn Summi
 t insights into hands‑on capability.\n\n--------------------------------
 -----------------------\n[Explore the Learn Path](https://learn.microsoft.
 com/plans/j2j1fz78ndwp8m/&wt.mc_id=meetup_26841_webpage_reactor)\n[Azure S
 killing - Build Your Azure Migrate and Modernize Skills](https://azure.git
 hub.io/MigrateModernizeSkilling/)\n[Microsoft Azure Summit: Migrate and Mo
 dernize with Agentic AI](https://www.microsoft.com/events/launch-events/mi
 grate-and-modernize-summit?msockid=0a79b602dee169e70531a109dfa968ea/&wt.mc
 _id=meetup_26841_webpage_reactor)\n\n📌 This session is a part of a seri
 es! Learn more [**here**](https://developer.microsoft.com/reactor/series/S
 -1644/?wt.mc_id=meetup_S-1644_webpage_reactor)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/microsoft-reactor-toronto/events/3134
 03856/
